benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/customFields - Remove custom fields from bundle

covered: Valid Deletion scenarios: TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05 cover removal of all fields, single field, and multiple fields (including the no-parameter case).

Input validation coverage: TC06 (invalid bundleId format), TC09 (invalid customField UUID format), TC22 (partial/truncated UUID bundleId), TC19 (empty customField), TC11 (extra, unsupported query parameters), TC21 (header length edge cases for X-Killbill-Comment).
Non-existent and empty-state handling: TC07 (non-existent bundle) and TC23 (state variation with no bundles).
Authorization and authentication coverage: TC08 (missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy header) and TC13 (invalid/expired authentication token).
Concurrency and integration scenarios: TC16 (concurrent deletions), TC24 (integration with degraded custom field storage), TC25 (data consistency after removal).

Edge cases and compatibility: TC14 (injection attempt in header), TC20 (maximum length for X-Killbill-Comment), TC18 (backward compatibility with omitting optional headers), TC10 (removing a field not present on the bundle), TC12 (service unavailability integration scenario), TC15 (performance with 1000 custom fields).
Regression scenarios: TC17 (removal affecting only targeted bundle) and TC25 (data consistency).
gaps: Soft-delete semantics and auditing: no explicit tests for soft-delete flags or audit trails after removal.
Authorization depth: only missing-header and invalid-token tested; lack of a dedicated 403 Forbidden scenario for insufficient permissions.
Caching behavior: no tests for ETag/Cache-Control headers or caching validation.
Rate limiting: no tests for throttling or 429 responses under bursty load.
Observability: no tests around logging/audit events or metrics collection.
Idempotency: repeated DELETE behavior (beyond concurrent deletion) not explicitly validated for full idempotency.
recommendations: Add an explicit 403 Forbidden test scenario to cover insufficient permission cases in addition to 401 Unauthorized.
Introduce rate-limiting/throttling tests (e.g., 429 Too Many Requests) to assess resilience under load.
Add tests for caching headers and behaviors (ETag, Cache-Control) and validation of cache-related responses.
Introduce soft-delete/audit-related tests to verify persistent flags or audit logs after removal.
Add dedicated idempotency-focused scenarios to confirm repeated DELETE requests remain safe and idempotent.
